</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,1675,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Host. Flies were attracted to a mixed aggregation of 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1059,1676,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Apis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mellifera">
<emphasis box="[921,1059,1676,1701]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. mellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pedro &amp; Camargo" authorityName="Pedro &amp; Camargo" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Partamona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiphytophila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Partamona epiphytophila</emphasis>
Pedro &amp; Camargo
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[611,701,1716,1741]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Plebeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[611,701,1716,1741]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Plebeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. Note that previous (
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[983,1154,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="14" refString="Brown, B. V. (2004 a) Revision of the subgenus Udamochiras of Melaloncha bee-killing flies (Diptera: Phoridae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 140, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="2004" yearSuffix="a">
Brown, 
<number box="[1080,1142,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown" box="[1167,1241,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="14" refString="Brown, B. V. (2004 b) Revision of the Melaloncha cingulata - group of bee-killing flies (Diptera: Phoridae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 97, 386 - 392." type="journal article" year="2004" yearSuffix="b">
<number box="[1167,1227,1715,1741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
) references to the bee fauna of Cumbre Alto Beni referred to the presence of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pedro &amp; Camargo. This" authorityName="Pedro &amp; Camargo. This" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Partamona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="combinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Partamona combinata</emphasis>
Pedro &amp; Camargo. This
</taxonomicName>
was an incorrect identification, however (verified by Camargo) and all references to 
<taxonomicName box="[632,785,1835,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Partamona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="combinata">
<emphasis box="[632,647,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[661,785,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">combinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be changed to 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1238,1835,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Partamona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiphytophila">
<emphasis box="[1048,1063,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1077,1238,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">epiphytophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
